Gillingham have signed Tottenham Hotspur defender Connor Ogilvie on a two-year deal. Ogilvie, 23, has spent the past two seasons on loan at the Gills having also had two spells with Stevenage. He becomes Steve Evansâ€™ first signing since taking over as manager at the Priestfield Stadium earlier this week. Ogilvie did not make a first-team appearance for Spurs having come through their academy but he has played more than 100 Football League games. Gillingham have not disclosed whether they paid a fee for Ogilvie, whose Spurs contract was set to end this summer.